article.description: Harrison's 16 leads St. John's past Niagara 70-57
article.headline: Harrison's 16 leads St. John's past Niagara 70-57
article.linkText: Harrison's 16 leads St. John's past Niagara 70-57
article.story: NEW YORK -- D'Angelo Harrison scored 13 of his 16 points in the first half and grabbed nine rebounds as St. John's pulled away from Niagara 70-57 Tuesday. With Harrison hitting 5 of 8 shots, the Red Storm (5-1) opened a 35-24 lead on the Purple Eagles (1-4) Niagara rallied in the second half to close within 46-45 on a Karonn Davis 3-pointer with 11:44 to play but Phil Greene IV had consecutive jumpers after a Rysheed Jordan free throw to put St. John's back up 51-45. When the Purple Eagles got it to 53-30 on a Wesley Myers 3, the Red Storm went on a 12-0 run, started by a Sir'Dominic Pointer bucket. He had six in the run with two dunks and Jordan's 3 made it 65-50 with 4:49 remaining. Emile Blackman had 21 points for Niagara and Ramone Snowden had 13 with 12 rebounds. Jamal Branch had 12 for St. John's.
